{{Not to be confused with|November 1|qq=November 1}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月初一|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 1일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November}} '''November 1''' is the 1st day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}} – the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Chōhō (era)|Chōhō]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:999|999]] [[:en:December 11|December 11]]) – [[:en:Fujiwara no Michinaga|Fujiwara no Michinaga]]’s daughter, [[:en:Empress Shōshi|Akiko]], was received into court.{{Citation needed|date=2021-03}} * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1863|1863]] [[:en:December 11|December 11]]) – The [[:en:Satsuma Domain|Satsuma Domain]] paid 100,000 dollars to an English envoy, resolving the [[:en:Namamugi Incident|Namamugi Incident]].{{Citation needed|date=2021-03}}
== Births == * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1561|1561]] [[December 7]]) – [[:en:Kikkawa Hiroie|Yoshikawa Hiroie]], the first lord of the [[:en:Suō Province|Suō Province]]’s {{ill|Iwakuni Domain|ja|岩国領|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwakuni Domain|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 岩国藩}} (died [[:en:1625|1625]]). * [[:en:Kenji (era)|Kenji]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1275|1275]] [[November 19]]) – [[:en:Musō Soseki|Musō Soseki]], a monk of the [[:en:Rinzai school|Rinzai Zen]] (died [[:en:1351|1351]]). * [[:en:Kōka|Kōka]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1847|1847]] [[December 8]]) – [[:en:Nakae Chōmin|Nakajima Chōmin]], a thinker (died [[:en:1901|1901]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Daireki|ja|大暦|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daireki|qq=}} 10th year ([[:en:776|776]]) – {{ill|Xinping Princess|ja|新平公主|zh|新平公主 (唐朝)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Xinping Princess|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, daughter of {{ill|Emperor Xuanzong|ja|玄宗|zh|玄宗 (唐)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Xuanzong|qq=}}. == Commemorations == * 朔旦冬至 (if this day coincides with the [[:en:Winter solstice|Winter Solstice]])
